Looping statement:
Looping statement is used when we have to execute a number of lines multiple times.
Till when,the given loop is executed depends on the given condition.
Interation of the loop is controlled in two way.
1>Entry control
  i)for loop
  ii)while loop
2>Exit control 
  i)do-while loop
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Every loop has mainly three parts:
1)initialization:Starting Point
2)condition:Ending point
3)updation:Increment/decrement /steps in each iteration 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 while loop:
It is entry control loop.That means given condition with loop is checked before block of while
execute.if given condition is  true then block of while is execute otherwise not.

Syntax:
initialization;
while(condition)
{
   //statement
   
   updation;
} 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
void main()
{
   int i=1;          //initialization
   
   while(i<=5)       //condition   true true true true true false
   {
      printf("ok");   //statement  ok ok ok ok ok 
	  i++;            //updation    2  3  4  5  6
   }
   printf("%d",i);    // Now i=6
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
for loop:
for loop is also an entry centrol loop,that means condition given within the loop
is checked first and if the given condition is true then the block of loop will be executed.
For Loop is easy to use.
Syntax:
for(initialization;condition;updation)
{

   //statement
   
}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
//WAP to print numbers from 1 to 20.

#include<stdio.h>
void main()
{
 int i;
 
 for(i=1;i<=20;i++)
 {
    printf("%d\t",i);
 }
 getch();
}
Example2:

#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
void main()
{
  int num,i,digit;
  clrscr();
  printf("Enter a number:");
  scanf("%d",&num);
  for(i=num;i>0;i=i/10)
  {
    digit=i%10;
    printf("%d\t",(digit*digit));	
  }
  getch();
}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
do-while Loop:
it is a exit control loop,in do-while loop given condition within the loop is checked after 
the execution of block of loop.
So,either the given condition is true or false,loop will be executed at least one time.
   
Syntax:
do
{
//statement

updation;   
}while(condition);   
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
#include<stdio.h>
void main()
{
   int i=1;
   clrscr();
   do
   {
      printf("It Executed at least One time !");
	  i++;
   }
   while(i>=20);
   getch();
}
output:
It is Executed at least one time !
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Nested loop:
Nested loop a structure of a program when any of the loop is difined within the 
block of another loop.

Syntax:

for(initialization;condition;updation) //outer loop
{

     //statement
    for(initializaion;condition;updation) //inner loop
	{
	   //statment
	}
    
	//statement
 
}



























































































































































